Police have arrested two suspected members of a notorious kidnap syndicate, Jato Abu Bello and Muhammad Suleiman, for their alleged roles in a series of kidnap cases in Ogun State. Police said the suspects were part of the gang that kidnapped one Ajibola Salimot Adejoke in Oke Ode area, off Ayetoro Road, Abeokutam on February 17. They also allegedly kidnapped one Victoria Oladoyin on February 26 in Aboba area of Abeokuta, and equally abducted two siblings, Esther Kehinde and David Kehinde, in Ayetoro on March 8, it was said.   Man who excreted 1,300kg of heroin jailed six years     Five killed as bandits open fire on passengers in Katsina     APC chair: Pressure mounts on Buhari to drop Adamu   The suspects, who reportedly confessed to the crimes, were arrested in the early hours of Saturday following intelligence. Police spokesman Abimbola Oyeyemi said yesterday that anti-kidnapping operatives in conjunction with officials of Ilupeju and Lafenwa police divisions stormed the suspectsâ€™ hideout where they arrested them. Oyeyemi said some of the victims have identified the suspects as their abductors.